values: Children count and subtract single digit numbers. Research has proven that counting single units as the primary strategy for solving arithmetic tasks helps children develop basic computational skills.

The lesson has a numeric puzzle through which children learn ordering, seriation, and basic sequencing of numbers 200 - 250.  Numbers are arranged in ascending order on a board.
